40|$|This chapter {{examines}} {{the kind of}} whistleblowing that is advocated by offering rewards to <b>whistleblowers.</b> The first section points at the link between our focus on efficiency and our growing unease with fraud. The second section discusses whistleblowing {{as a source of}} information in that context. The third section comments on the US False Claims Act. The fourth section points out some pitfalls of rewarding <b>whistleblowers.</b> I conclude in a balanced way, recognizing both the bright and the dark side of rewarding <b>whistleblowers</b> but generally warning it is not the panacea...|$|R
